sentences: John Mooney (born April 3, 1955) is an American blues guitarist and singer based in New Orleans, Louisiana.
The following year, he met Son House, a Mississippi bluesman who became a huge musical influence on him.
In 1976, Mooney moved to New Orleans, and soon he was playing with host of musicians in the New Orleans R&B circuit including Earl King, The Meters, Snooks Eaglin and Professor Longhair.
He released his first album, Comin' Your Way, on Blind Pig Records in 1979.
In 1981, he formed his own band, Bluesiana, with whom he has been recording and touring since.
In 2000, he returned to Blind Pig to release Gone to Hell which featured Dr. John as a special guest.
All I Want followed two years later on the label.
His album, Big Ol' Fiya, was nominated for a Blues Music Award for "Contemporary Blues Album of the Year" in 2007.
